  "configSectionsAdded": [],
  "migrationGuide": "## Trellis → Polygon: full rebrand\n\n0.7.0 renames the workflow directory and every managed asset. `polygon update --migrate` does it all in one pass:\n\n### 1. `.trellis/` → `.polygon/`\nThe whole workflow directory is renamed in place **before** the version check runs, so your tasks, spec, workspace, journal, config and runtime move atomically. No data is copied or deleted.\n\n### 2. `trellis-*` → `polygon-*` assets\nEvery skill, agent and command directory/file gains the `polygon-` name across all platforms (156 rename entries). Unmodified files are renamed silently; files you customized land on the standard `Modified by you` confirm prompt — pressing Enter (backup-rename) keeps your edits at the new path.\n\n### 3. Things to update yourself\n- **Repo-root `.gitignore`**: if it lists `.trellis/`, change it to `.polygon/` (update warns you when it detects this).\n- **`update.skip` in config.yaml**: if you pinned `.trellis/...` paths, repoint them to `.polygon/...`.\n- **Scripts/CI** calling the `trellis` or `tl` command: switch to `polygon`.\n- **Anything reading `TRELLIS_*` env vars**: switch to `POLYGON_*`.\n\n### How to upgrade\n```bash\npolygon update --migrate\n```\n`--migrate` is required (breaking release). The rename is idempotent — re-running is a no-op.",
  "aiInstructions": "This is the Polygon rebrand release. After `polygon update --migrate`: the workflow dir is now `.polygon/` (was `.trellis/`), and all skills/agents/commands use the `polygon-` prefix (was `trellis-`). When referencing workflow paths, skills, or the CLI, always use the polygon names. If the user's repo-root .gitignore or config.yaml `update.skip` still mentions `.trellis/`, point that out so they can fix it. The `trellis`/`tl` commands no longer exist — use `polygon`.",
  "notes": "Breaking. Run `polygon update --migrate`. The `.trellis/` → `.polygon/` directory rename happens automatically as a pre-step; the 156 asset renames run through the normal migration flow. Idempotent and data-safe (atomic rename, no copy/delete of user data)."
}
